1.2.42
- RGMercs pause support (based on Hazado's contribution): when rgmercs is
  RUNNING, loot/give/reclaim use /rgl pause|unpause; otherwise /e3p on|off.
  TurboGive pauses the remote box via /lua run turbo_bot_pause so each client
  decides locally. Shared helpers in turbo_lib/bot_pause.lua + mac Subs.

1.2.41
- Zone lag fix: autoLaunch no longer treats post-zone group-roster churn as
  "everyone joined" (empty roster no longer wipes last_sig; staggered
  repopulation settles for peer_autostart_settle_s before soft-launch).
- turbogear_autostart is truly idempotent: healthy bg → noop (was forcing a
  full inventory publish via /tgearbg publish). Inventory still self-heals via
  dirty watch, startup, REQUEST, bank capture, and manual sync.
- Metadata heartbeats now carry zoneShortName/zoneName, and the bg fires one
  meta heartbeat on real zone change so same-zone handoff guards stay fresh
  without a full inventory republish.
- Slim loot doctor: /turbodoctor loot (aliases: /tlootwhy, /lua run Turbo
  doctor loot). Prints AUTO READY + first failing slain-event gate, live
  Turbo/CombatLoot/Mode/Looter/LootRadius, corpse+aggro counts, hide mode,
  and closest npccorpse distance when radius count is 0.

1.2.40
- Pill row decluttered: the Full Names/Compact toggle is now a "Compact"
  checkbox in the List pill's new VIEW section (Full names by default; routes
  through the existing density+names toggle). Missing Only stays on the row -
  it is a working filter people flip constantly.
- Roster legend moved to a tooltip on the "Slot" column header (covers normal
  and ultra layouts, includes the right-click hints); the footer legend row is
  gone, giving the roster that vertical space back.

1.2.39
- List pill FIXED (root cause found via pilldebug close-reason logging): MQ's
  ImGui.Selectable returns true every frame for a row drawn selected=true, so
  the active "BiS Catalog" mode row fired continuously and closed the panel the
  moment it opened ("panel CLOSED (entry selected)"). All pill selectables now
  guard with "if not selected", the same pattern characters.lua already used -
  which is also why the Characters popup never had the bug.

1.2.38
- List pill: open-state moved to _G so module reloads can no longer reset it
  (the 1.2.37 panel opened then vanished; repeated "CLICK: panel opening" with
  no "panel closing" proved state was being wiped between clicks). The
  hot-reload shim now retries a stale VERSION once per session instead of
  every frame - the per-frame reload was the state-wiper. pilldebug now logs
  the REASON for every close (entry selected / click-away with hover states)
  and prints a line on module load so reload loops are visible.

1.2.37
- List pill: converted from OpenPopup/BeginPopup to a manually-managed dropdown
  panel. /tgear pilldebug proved the popup opened and was externally closed one
  frame later (CLICK -> OPEN -> CLOSED every click); the manual panel is immune
  since only the pill's own code closes it (pick an entry, click the pill again,
  or click anywhere outside). pilldebug now logs panel OPEN/CLOSED transitions.

1.2.36
- BiS + Lists: Missing Only + Compact/Full Names moved onto the pill row, right
  of the List pill (hidden in Manage Lists mode). Same settings keys.
- Parked the DoN faction/crystals experiment: roster headers render identically
  on every catalog again (no second line). Removed the Magelo fetcher, the
  /tgear faction command, and the faction chat event. Snapshots still carry
  radiant/ebon crystal counts for cache compatibility; nothing reads them.
  Magelo/header-extra modules and tests removed.
- New /tgear pilldebug: gated List-pill diagnostics. Toggle it, click the pill:
  a CLICK line without a popup OPEN line means the popup is killed same-frame;
  no CLICK line means input never reaches the button. Report which you see.

